Classpublic class Rendition

The Rendition object represents one of the multi-bitrate streaming renditions of a video.

Constructor detail
Rendition()constructor
public function Rendition(url:String, audioOnly:Boolean, controllerType:CDNControllerTypeEnum, encodingRate:Number, frameHeight:Number, frameWidth:Number, size:Number, id:Number, referenceId:String, videoCodec:VideoCodecTypeEnum, videoContainer:VideoContainerTypeEnum, videoDuration:Number = 0, remoteStreamName:String = "", remoteUrl:String = "", uploadTimestampMillis:Number = 0, displayName:String = "")

Class constructor, create an instance of a Cue Point.

Parameters
url:String — The URL of the rendition file.
 
audioOnly:Boolean — If true, this rendition is audio-only and has no video content. Audio-only renditions can be used for mobile streaming over low-bandwidth connections. It is recommended that videos in iOS applications should include a 64 kbps audio-only rendition.
 
controllerType:CDNControllerTypeEnum — The value of the controllerType field in the Rendition object can depend on how you are delivering content and what CDN you are using.
 
encodingRate:Number — The rendition's encoding rate, in bits per second.
 
frameHeight:Number — The rendition's display height, in pixels.
 
frameWidth:Number — The rendition's display width, in pixels.
 
size:Number — Required. The file size of the rendition, in bytes.
 
id:Number — The identifier for the Rendition
 
referenceId:String — The reference identifier for the Rendition
 
videoCodec:VideoCodecTypeEnum — Required. Valid values are SORENSON, ON2, and H264.
 
videoContainer:VideoContainerTypeEnum — The length of the remote video asset in milliseconds.
 
videoDuration:Number (default = 0) — The format of the wrapper that provides metadata and describes how the video and audio are stored in the file. Valid values are FLV, MP4, and M2TS.
 
remoteStreamName:String (default = "") — [Optional — required for streaming remote assets only] A stream name for Flash streaming appended to the value of the remoteUrl property.
 
remoteUrl:String (default = "") — Required, for remote assets. The complete path to the file hosted on the remote server. If the file is served using progressive download, then you must include the file name and extension for the file. You can also use a URL that re-directs to a URL that includes the file name and extension. If the file is served using Flash streaming, use the remoteStreamName attribute to provide the stream name.
 
uploadTimestampMillis:Number (default = 0) — The timestamp of the upload as Millis
 
displayName:String (default = "") — A display name for the rendition
